    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## FLOW 4: Registration + Email Confirmation & Resend (Mailjet)\nMirrors the app's signup (script.js handleRegister / resendConfirmation), but surfaces the Mailjet email send as its own visible node for the demo.\n\n- **Register**: `Supabase Admin: Generate Link` -> `Build Confirmation Email` -> `Send via Mailjet` -> respond.\n- **Resend**: same chain, regenerating a fresh link for an unconfirmed account.\n\n### Why admin generate_link (not /signup)?\nIn the live app, Mailjet is Supabase's custom SMTP relay, so calling `/auth/v1/signup` makes Supabase AUTO-SEND the confirmation email (invisible to n8n). To show the Mailjet send as an explicit step WITHOUT sending a duplicate, this flow uses `/auth/v1/admin/generate_link` (type=signup): it creates the user and RETURNS the confirmation `action_link` but does NOT auto-send. The `Build Confirmation Email` Code node injects that link into the branded template (SQL/email-template-confirm-signup.html), and `Send via Mailjet` POSTs it to the Mailjet Send API v3.1.\n\n### Setup before running\n1. Replace `YOUR_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` (both Generate Link nodes) with the Supabase SERVICE ROLE key. It is a SECRET - server-side only; never ship it in the browser app.\n2. Create an n8n **Basic Auth** credential named \"Mailjet API (key:secret)\": username = Mailjet API Key, password = Mailjet Secret Key.\n3. The `From` address is `ClearCare+ <clearcareplus.de@gmail.com>` (your Mailjet-verified sender). Recipients see it as \"via bnc3.mailjet.com\" until a custom domain/DKIM is set up in Mailjet.\n\nSame email, same template, same outcome as the live app - the mechanic is just made visible here.",
        "height": 620,
        "width": 332,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "be6e4219-08a1-415f-a340-81cc1aa7bf05",
      "name": "Sticky Note Flow4",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1296,
        2752
      ]
    },
